# Nuxt 4 Atomic Project Conventions

Content-agnostic rules for Nuxt 4 + Vue 3 + Tailwind marketing/portfolio sites with a headless CMS.

## Architecture

- **atoms/** — props-only, NO slots, no business logic, no CMS
- **molecules/** — compose atoms; slot only for layout shells (Card)
- **organisms/** — page sections (header, hero, grids, modals)
- **backgrounds/** — client-only effects; dynamic import heavy libs; cleanup on unmount
- Feature domains (experiments, tools) get separate folders — not mixed into atoms

Nuxt auto-import prefixes: `AtomsButton`, `OrganismsSiteHeader`, `BackgroundsVantaBirds`.

## Slots

Prefer props. Atoms must not use `<slot>`. If an atom needs a slot, move it to molecules.

## Design tokens

Use semantic Tailwind tokens from `tailwind.config.js`: `ink`, `surface`, `elevated`, `border-subtle`, `border-default`, `accent`, `accent-hover`, `accent-muted`, `content`, `content-muted`.

FORBIDDEN in components/pages: `bg-gray-*`, `text-gray-*`, `bg-blue-*`, hardcoded brand hex in templates.

Use `@layer components` utilities in `main.css`: `.page-title`, `.card`, `.btn-primary`.

## Layout

`layouts/default.vue` = shell only (background tag, header, main, footer, SEO). No CDN scripts, no animation init in layout.

Avoid `min-h-screen` on short pages — causes unnecessary footer scroll.

## CMS & secrets

Tokens/endpoints in `.env` (gitignored) + `.env.example`. Never commit bearer tokens. Components consume composables, not raw config.

## Hygiene

- `<script setup>` only
- No `v-html` for third-party embeds
- No dead components
- Accessibility: skip link, `#main-content`, focus-visible rings, aria on menus

## Copy mindset

Speak to humans, not engineers. Hero = one accent phrase, not a skill list. Benefits over jargon in cards.

## Before shipping

Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build`. Grep for rogue palette classes and slots in atoms.
